The paper discusses the application of complexity theory in machine learning, specifically in the areas of regression and classification. This falls under the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of algorithmic probability and non-smooth manifolds, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of numerical methods and exploitation techniques for algorithmic search also falls under the category of "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS) and "Computational Complexity" (cs.CC).
